      "content": "That's a bit too vague, though. If a reporter asks point-blank, \"The candidate said 'no' last week, why are they saying 'yes' now?\" and we just say they're \"unwavering,\" they're gonna call us out on the contradiction immediately. We need a specific reason for the change that doesn't make it look like they're just changing their mind to suit whoever's paying. What's the actual narrative here?",
